
Install Python 2.7 as well as the libraries

-numpy >= 1.11.0
-scipy >= 0.17.0
-matplotlib >=1.5.1
-pandas >= 0.17.0
-Tkinter
-PIL


Compile the c++ executables:

- Open a terminal
- navigate into to /src
- Compile using the command lines below

Command lines to compile are: 
	make -f Makefile

Command lines to clean up are: 
	make -f Makefile clean
	

To run the code:
- Open a terminal
- Navigate to the directory containing DSM_simulator.py
- Type python DSM_simulator.py

**** CAREFUL **** The code overwrites the results directory "/Results_CITY" if it already exists!

